Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.13,0:00:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}BEYOND JOURNEY'S END{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.17,0:00:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[♪ opening theme song playing]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.84,0:01:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}EPISODE 30:\NTHE HERO OF THE SOUTH{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.84,0:01:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.05,0:01:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[birds chirping]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.39,0:01:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[OLD MAN] We have a statue\Nin dire need of a good polish.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.14,0:01:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}What's the reward?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[OLD MAN] A spell to scratch\Nthe hard-to-reach,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.15,0:01:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}itchy parts on your back.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.07,0:01:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[OLD MAN] Hmm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.61,0:01:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}29 YEARS AFTER THE DEATH\NOF HIMMEL THE HERO,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.57,0:01:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}IN FABEL VILLAGE, LOCATED\NIN THE NORTHERN LANDS{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.37,0:02:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I guess we're back\Nto odd jobs, then.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.37,0:02:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Seems there are rusty statues\Nof Mr. Himmel in every town.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.00,0:02:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}True! It'll be nice\Nto use our hands{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.05,0:02:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}for more than axe\Nand staff slinging.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.59,0:02:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}All right. Time to clean!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.93,0:02:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The statue's made of bronze,\Nso we can use magic.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You won't have\Nto lift a single finger.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.64,0:02:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Uh?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.68,0:02:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Uh...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.65,0:02:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] That guy isn't Himmel!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.19,0:02:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Is this your\Nfirst time seeing him?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.44,0:02:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's the Hero of the South.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.32,0:02:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[BOTH] Hmm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.95,0:02:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Though Himmel was the one\Nwho defeated the Demon King,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.12,0:02:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}he was not the only hero.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Dozens of brave souls\Nmade the attempt before him.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.62,0:02:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But of them all,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.17,0:02:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the Hero of the South was said\Nto be humanity's strongest.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.67,0:02:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK]\NThat seems a bit extreme.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.97,0:02:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'd have to disagree.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.97,0:02:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}In my opinion,\Nhe was worthy of the title.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}At the time, a fearsome group\Nposed a threat to humanity.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.06,0:03:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The Seven Sages of Destruction.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.31,0:03:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They controlled\Nthe major regions{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.94,0:03:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}around the northern lands.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.73,0:03:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Despite all our\Ngreatest efforts,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.65,0:03:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}we only managed to defeat\Ntwo members of their band.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.16,0:03:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Of the other five, two vanished.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.24,0:03:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We assumed they either fled\Nor tucked themselves away.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.20,0:03:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Guess one of those was\NAura the Guillotine.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.29,0:03:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] The Hero of the South\Nwas powerful enough{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.92,0:03:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to defeat the remaining three.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.92,0:03:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[children laughing]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.25,0:03:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}His rapid advance was\Nunlike anything I've ever seen.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.30,0:03:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}In just a year,\Nhe completely annihilated{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.55,0:03:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the Demon King's\Nfront-line troops.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.26,0:03:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That cleared a pathway\Nto the very top{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.26,0:03:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}of the Northern Plateau,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.02,0:03:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the heart of the\NDemon King's supply route.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.73,0:03:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.31,0:03:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's where he was defeated\Nby Schlacht the Omniscient,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.36,0:03:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the Demon King's confidant{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.74,0:03:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}who could see a thousand years\Ninto the future,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.45,0:03:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}making him a fearsome foe.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}At the hands of Schlacht\Nand the Seven Sages,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}he met his end.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.41,0:04:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}He fought against all seven?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.45,0:04:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}No wonder he kicked the bucket.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NIt wasn't a quick fight.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}He still defeated\Nthree of them, remember?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.75,0:04:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The battle only ended\Nwhen he and Schlacht{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.34,0:04:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}took each other's lives.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.18,0:04:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}His valiant efforts that day{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}liberated many people\Nin this region{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.89,0:04:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}from the tyranny\Nof the Seven Sages.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.23,0:04:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It only makes sense{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.35,0:04:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the villagers here\Nare devoted to him.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.07,0:04:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Because the Hero\Nof the South's body{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}was never recovered,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.32,0:04:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}legend claims he's\Nstill fighting tooth and nail{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.95,0:04:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}with Schlacht the Omniscient\Nto this day.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.37,0:04:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Though I highly doubt\Nit's that romantic.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.58,0:04:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}His opponents had a keen taste\Nfor human flesh.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.71,0:04:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I imagine they ate\Nevery last piece of the hero.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.13,0:04:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Shall we get the old boy\Ncleaned up?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] I refuse.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.47,0:05:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I cannot defeat the Demon King.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.52,0:05:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Hmm... I knew that\Nthis would happen.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.44,0:05:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}And I knew I'd never\Nconjure up the right words{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.65,0:05:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to convince\Na complete enigma like you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.07,0:05:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You speak\Nas if you already knew{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.82,0:05:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}exactly how\Nthis would play out.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.87,0:05:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I suppose it seems that way\Nbecause I did.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.12,0:05:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Hmm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You seem the type\Nto carefully guard a secret.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.63,0:05:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Hm?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.13,0:05:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HERO OF THE SOUTH]\NI could serve{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.21,0:05:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}my most hidden\Nconfessions to you{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}on a silver platter,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and you would\Nnever tell a soul.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.26,0:05:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}So I shall confide in you,\Nand you alone.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.51,0:05:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}There's only one reason\Nthat I have come to be{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.64,0:05:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}humanity's strongest hero.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.48,0:05:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I walk in the present,\Nyet see the future.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.07,0:06:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}My!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.32,0:06:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's quite impressive.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.28,0:06:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Hm?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.03,0:06:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You don't believe\NI'm telling the truth?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.37,0:06:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Frieren blows]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.62,0:06:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}No, I believe you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.66,0:06:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I just can't bring myself\Nto care.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.54,0:06:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Allow me\Nto pique your interest,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.50,0:06:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}for the near future holds\Nmuch for you and me.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You know of the Seven Sages\Nof Destruction, yes?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.76,0:06:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.01,0:06:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}One year from now,\Non the Northern Plateau,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.60,0:06:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I will be slain along with\NSchlacht the Omniscient.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.44,0:06:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They shall rip me\Nfrom the world{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I have fought\Nso hard to protect.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.40,0:06:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.60,0:07:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Fate has decreed I'm to die\Nwithout achieving my goal.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.68,0:07:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.98,0:07:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Don't feel sorry for me.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.53,0:07:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Even if you were to join me\Non my journey,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I fear the truth of my demise\Nis already set in stone.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.78,0:07:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Forget me.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.58,0:07:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Soon, a much younger,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}sunnier hero\Nwill pay you a visit.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.33,0:07:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.92,0:07:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Though, it terribly pains\Nmy soul to admit,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.54,0:07:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}it is he who will save\Nthe world, and not I.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.26,0:07:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}He will successfully\Nconvince you{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.05,0:07:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to travel with his party,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.89,0:07:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and that party will defeat\Nthe Demon King.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.55,0:07:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I honestly\Ncan't see that happening.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.60,0:07:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HERO OF THE SOUTH]\NYou'll see once you meet him.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.27,0:08:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That young man is going to\Nchange your life for good.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.06,0:08:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.28,0:08:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Well, then,\Nthe clock is ticking.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Before I go,\Nmay I ask you a favor?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.54,0:08:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] What is it?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HERO OF THE SOUTH]\NWhen you meet that young man,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.75,0:08:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}give him this message.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.89,0:08:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.14,0:08:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HERO OF THE SOUTH]\NYou have my word.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.86,0:08:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I will clear a path for you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Put your faith\Nin humanity's strongest,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.91,0:08:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the Hero of the South.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.75,0:09:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Even if my contributions\Nare buried{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.04,0:09:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}in the shadows of history,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.79,0:09:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}it will be well worth it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.47,0:09:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark laughing]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[BOY 1] Hey! Get back here!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.43,0:09:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[BOY 2] You'll never get away!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.76,0:09:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Frieren chuckles softly]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.43,0:09:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NSome foresight you had.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You are as present here as ever.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.61,0:09:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}History hasn't forgotten\Na thing.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.95,0:09:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}29 YEARS AFTER THE DEATH\NOF HIMMEL THE HERO,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.86,0:09:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}IN GRAF DACH'S DOMAIN, LOCATED\NIN THE NORTHERN LANDS{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.95,0:09:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The last time we were in\Na big city was ages ago.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.95,0:09:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NWe're leaving as soon as{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}we replenish our supplies.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.25,0:09:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Seriously? I'd be okay\Nwith taking it slow.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.21,0:09:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Hey.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.34,0:09:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They've even got magic shops.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.55,0:09:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Summon your focus, Stark.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Don't you know\Ntime is a finite resource?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.47,0:09:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Yeah, I'm well-aware.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:09:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Fern grunts softly]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.60,0:10:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.62,0:10:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Well, that's everything.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.87,0:10:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Come on.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.08,0:10:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}At least let us grab\Nsomething nice to eat{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.71,0:10:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}before we leave town.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Not a chance.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.92,0:10:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We've no coin to spare.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We must be economical,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.26,0:10:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}or our pockets will be empty\Nwhen we need them full.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.09,0:10:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You've sure turned over\Na new leaf.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.76,0:10:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Quick. Let's go.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}She's been acting strange\Nthis whole time.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.19,0:10:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Something's off.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.48,0:10:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Normally, she'd want\Nto stay and explore{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.15,0:10:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}a big city like this\Nfor a few months or longer.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.02,0:10:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.65,0:10:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We were so close.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.61,0:10:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You must be\Nthe illustrious Miss Frieren.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.78,0:11:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}My lord has formally invited you\Nto dinner at his home.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.87,0:11:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] We're not hungry.\NAnd we're in a hurry.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.46,0:11:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It is truly a shame.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.96,0:11:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}He says Miss Frieren was\Na member of the party of heroes{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.42,0:11:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}that saved this land years ago.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.17,0:11:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}He merely wishes to give\Nhis thanks to all three of you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.89,0:11:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Frieren sighs]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.81,0:11:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[insects trilling]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.81,0:11:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[knife slicing softly]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Mm. Now that's what\NI'm talkin' about!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.82,0:11:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Dach chuckles]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.07,0:11:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Thank you for\Nthe kind invitation, Graf Dach.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.82,0:11:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Sincerely.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.53,0:11:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] She looks\Nterribly unhappy.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.20,0:11:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I should thank you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.16,0:11:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You helped my great grandpa.\NI'm eternally grateful.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.41,0:11:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}So, what do you want?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.62,0:11:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Dach chuckles]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.92,0:11:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I admire those who can get\Nstraight to the point.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.71,0:11:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The truth is, my family's\Ntreasured heirloom sword{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.67,0:11:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}has been stolen from us\Nby a demon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.05,0:11:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You allowed it\Nto be stolen again?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.18,0:11:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Hmm. "Again?"{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.93,0:12:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It was stolen from\Nhis great-grandpa, too.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They just don't live and learn.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.77,0:12:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Very well.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.48,0:12:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You can reward me\Nwith a grimoire.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.19,0:12:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Seems like a fair price.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] What a pain.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I've found many of the nobles\Nin the northern lands{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to be extremely pushy.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.91,0:12:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But I recall this family\Nhas always made{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.71,0:12:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}particularly unreasonable\Ndemands.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If you don't get\Nmy sword back,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.75,0:12:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I will throw you\Nin the dungeon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.55,0:12:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-[HIMMEL] Huh?\N-[EISEN] Talk about tyrannical.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.72,0:12:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}At least they were able\Nto point us in the direction{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.85,0:12:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}that the demon fled\Nthis time around.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.76,0:12:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We were given no leads before.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.44,0:12:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The aimlessness of our search{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.02,0:12:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}conjures images\Nof needles and haystacks.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.28,0:12:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Ultimately,\Nwe did find the sword.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.11,0:13:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It was at the top\Nof the Schwer Mountains.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.95,0:13:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}What a waste of energy.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.12,0:13:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Huh.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.54,0:13:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I wonder why the demons\Nhave stolen the sword again.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.25,0:13:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] The sword wasn't\Nthe Dach Family's originally.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It once belonged\Nto a famous demon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It must possess some appeal\Nonly demons understand.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.09,0:13:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You know, when he mentioned\Nthis job,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.43,0:13:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I was sure\Nyou would turn it down.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.10,0:13:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Frieren inhales\Nand exhales deeply]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.14,0:13:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I didn't have a real choice.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.43,0:13:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}This is the very same sword\NHimmel retrieved.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.77,0:13:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If I had let it stay stolen,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.61,0:13:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}his efforts would've been\Nfor naught.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Besides, Himmel wouldn't\Nabandon someone in need.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.32,0:13:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.41,0:14:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We're too late.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.33,0:14:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's already been destroyed.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.21,0:14:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] There's nobody left.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.84,0:14:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-[rustling]\N-[birds cawing]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.59,0:14:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}No. I can sense one.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.77,0:14:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Are you from this village?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.57,0:15:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[WOMAN] No.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.65,0:15:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'm a traveling priest.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.61,0:15:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}And who are you?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.74,0:15:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Just adventurers\Npassing through.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.28,0:15:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Look around.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.04,0:15:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}This is the work\Nof the Sword Demon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.42,0:15:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I came here to mourn\Nthe innocent lives they stole.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.00,0:15:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You said "Sword Demon?"{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.76,0:15:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That sounds like the very demon\Nwe came here to slay.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.59,0:15:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[WOMAN]\NThe sword demon has destroyed{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}countless villages\Nin this region.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.89,0:15:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}There has never been\Na single survivor.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.02,0:15:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] How awful.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.40,0:15:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[WOMAN]\NBrave adventurers...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.73,0:15:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Will you offer a prayer\Nfor their souls?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Wait, did I miss something?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] As I thought,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.66,0:15:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}there are no bodies\Nburied here.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.04,0:15:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] Why not?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.46,0:16:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Because the traveling priest\Nis the Sword Demon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.00,0:16:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Fern and Stark gasp]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.13,0:16:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Not the type to leave corpses,\Nare you?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.43,0:16:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I was nearly starving\Nwhen I killed them.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.64,0:16:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I did what I had to do\Nin order to survive.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Even though\Nyou don't have to eat humans?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.98,0:16:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[SWORD DEMON]\NPerhaps I don't have to,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.90,0:16:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}but that doesn't mean\NI shouldn't.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.11,0:16:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Speaking to it\Nis a waste of time.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.49,0:16:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Destroy it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.79,0:16:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark grunting]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.01,0:16:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] It's quick.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.18,0:16:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Fern gasps]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.60,0:16:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark grunting]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.65,0:17:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Thanks for that.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.40,0:17:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Don't mention it.\NIt's what I'm here for.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[shivering] So cold.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.63,0:17:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}This was a truly awful job.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.59,0:17:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Agreed. But at least\Nwe defeated a demon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.90,0:17:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HIMMEL] It was an inconvenience\Nat the moment.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But down the road,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.19,0:17:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}our efforts today\Ncould save lives.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.94,0:17:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.90,0:17:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You never know.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.24,0:17:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's why I can't abandon\Nsomeone who needs me.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.12,0:18:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[chuckles] Or maybe your joy\Nmerely grows with our sorrow.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The challenge\Nis what makes it exciting.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.25,0:18:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Exciting for who?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.72,0:18:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Expertly done, you two.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.56,0:18:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You fired first. Why?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.19,0:18:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The demon hadn't escalated\Nthe situation at all.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.94,0:18:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Because I knew you and Stark\Nwere about to pray.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.74,0:18:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-I had no choice but to act.\N-[Fern exclaims softly]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.32,0:18:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.00,0:18:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Typically,\Nwhen people go to pray,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.79,0:18:44.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}they close their eyes.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.67,0:18:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The demon knew that\Nand took advantage of it{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.21,0:18:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to kill and consume\Ncompassionate travelers.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.21,0:18:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark exclaims softly]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.93,0:19:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.56,0:19:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[chuckles]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.19,0:19:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}My treasured heirloom\Nis home at last.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.94,0:19:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'm ever in your debt.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.69,0:19:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Thanks to you...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.24,0:19:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}our beloved city\Nis safe once more.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.78,0:19:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Frieren chuckles]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.53,0:19:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[footsteps]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.37,0:19:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Could you please\Ndrop us off at the marketplace?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.75,0:19:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Why certainly, ma'am.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.17,0:19:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] At the end of the day,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.67,0:19:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the Graf seemed\Nquite happy with us.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.09,0:19:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I just hope he keeps a close eye\Non his sword.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.68,0:19:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I have a feeling that\Nif the demons want it so badly,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}they'll try to steal it again.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.64,0:19:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}There's no doubt.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.39,0:19:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That was the second time\Nthey succeeded.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.77,0:19:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But the town has faced\Nmany an attack.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] Hmm?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.23,0:19:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}So as long as the Graf\Nhangs onto that sword,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.65,0:19:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the demons will keep trying\Nto take it back?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.99,0:19:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I understand\Nit's a treasured heirloom,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.82,0:19:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}but if it's that dangerous,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.12,0:20:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}maybe they should\Nget rid of it already.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.16,0:20:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Unfortunately,\Nit's not that simple.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.74,0:20:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Is it not?\NI suppose you would know.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.66,0:20:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Nobles can be so protective\Nover their riches.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.25,0:20:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They're stubborn\Nin that regard.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.05,0:20:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That much is true.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.96,0:20:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But if they dispose of it\Nor send it away,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.09,0:20:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}they risk letting it fall\Ninto the hands of a demon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.55,0:20:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Hm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.39,0:20:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}When a demon\Nacquires power like that,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}you can bet\Nthey are going to show it off.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.39,0:20:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Mm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.64,0:20:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.69,0:20:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Is that the nature\Nof all demons?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.15,0:20:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The last time a demon\Nhad the sword,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.44,0:20:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}it started out\Non a similar rampage.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.86,0:20:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Three villages were destroyed.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.07,0:20:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}A town was razed to the ground.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.70,0:20:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's insane.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.83,0:20:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The Graf was mortified.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.70,0:20:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}A traitor helped the demon\Nprocure the weapon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.17,0:20:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}A servant of the Graf\Nfell for its kind words{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.67,0:20:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and manufactured charm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.21,0:20:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.30,0:21:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Ever since then,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.84,0:21:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Graf Dach's family\Nhas prioritized{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.06,0:21:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}protecting the heirloom sword.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.56,0:21:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[indistinct chatter]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.02,0:21:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Perhaps the mission\Nhas outgrown the family.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.94,0:21:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It seems to have become\Nthe duty of the whole city.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.48,0:21:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Huh?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.45,0:21:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You think this demon had help?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Was there a traitor\Nlike last time around?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.95,0:21:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'm not sure.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.08,0:21:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That said,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.91,0:21:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}as long as humankind\Nknows desire,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.58,0:21:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}the demons will\Ntake advantage of it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.46,0:21:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark sighs]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.59,0:21:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Humans struggle\Nto resist their impulses.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.67,0:21:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Much like the demons.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.55,0:21:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If it happens again,\NI hope you come back.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.64,0:21:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They'll need you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.60,0:21:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That shall depend on the reward.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.81,0:21:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We all know you would\Ncome flying back{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.56,0:21:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}for any old grimoire.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.52,0:21:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Who can say?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.27,0:21:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Though they did give me{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.52,0:22:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}an exceptionally interesting one\Nthis time.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.61,0:22:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[sniffs]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.24,0:22:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'm glad, Mistress.\NWhat is it, then?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.07,0:22:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Something we can really use?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.66,0:22:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.91,0:22:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Oh, yes.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.54,0:22:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}A miraculous spell\Nthat can turn{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.46,0:22:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}a red apple into\Na green one.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.08,0:22:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] That's a no, then.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.09,0:22:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[♪ closing theme song playing]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.97,0:23:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[MAN] This brings me back.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.10,0:23:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK]\NI think I'd like to visit.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.27,0:23:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NYou just called me a grandma.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.43,0:23:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[overlapping chatter]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.56,0:23:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HEITER] You promised\Nit would be quick!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.69,0:23:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HIMMEL] There's something here.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.69,0:23:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\N"Somewhere She'd Like."{\b0}
